caption: We had a great experience here when stopping in for drinks and an appetizer. All the staff were very friendly and fantastic. While we just had an app, the menu was diverse and appealing with drink specials to compliment the menu. *while there take a moment to check out the basement...such a quirky cool contrast to the upstairs!

Nice atmosphere, friendly hospitality, but not recommended for families with kids being food is way over priced... meal for family of 4 bill was $128... For 1soda,  3 waters, 3 burgers and a new York strip, kids chicken strip, and 3 sides of mac&cheese.
Great food, and experience all around
Great atmosphere and good food. Lobster Mac & Cheese was outstanding. East Coast oysters were great too.

The wife and I have been here twice and it is an absolute gem. Their 1/2 price seafood towers during happy hour are really fresh. The salmon chowder is amazing, and the cocktails are spot on. I would definitely recommend dinner here
Delicious food and a great bloody mary. Very friendly and attentive staff.

Very ambitious menu that they mostly pull off beautifully. Try the cheese curds and the biscuits - mouth watering. Service can be a little spotty, but they go out of their way to keep you happy and coming back. All in all, it's a must-try in IC.

Maybe it's COVID fatigue, but our recent yep here was above and beyond expectations. Fish and chips to die for, and our kids' meals cooked to perfection. Great service, never pushy, and extremely knowledgeable about the menu for just an all around great experience. Will return.

Bartender was great.  Knowledgeable pleasant, and engaging. He made our drinks perfectly including an off menu classic cocktail without skipping a beat and went on to discuss with us the hibiscus infused tequila used in one of our drinks as well as giving a sample of it on its own so we could see what it brings to the drink.

Nice fancy restaurant but didn't expect it to be cool also. Honestly from first judgement thought it would be a stuck up, fancy place but only went in for a drink and the people were cool. The place has a basement that is pretty cool also.
Amazing food!

the food amazing but the amount of chicken that they added was perfect! Loved how they put the peanuts in a small container incase anyone is allergic. They were accurate on the waiting time and they were super friendly. Outside seating during the pandemic with beautiful lights
Incredible food, drinks and service!!! Definitely my go to place for all seasons!  Perfect for a cozy winter day or and a beautiful day in the summer/spring/fall on the patio! ☀️

Absolutely phenomenal food and service. My partner and I rarely get time for dates due to conflicting schedules but this place has been amazing every time we go, from the moment we walk in to the moment we leave with our desserts. Super classy but still a comfortable formal vibe. The bartender was amazing with drink recommendations as well as serving us and even remembering us from months in between visits, the host came down and talked whiskeys, and bourbons with me, and the kitchen kept bringing out amazing dishes (bay biscuits and shrimp cocktail, Cesar salad with the most tender and well seasoned salmon, without over doing it) simply blown away and will continue to come back. Gotta get the truffle fries, and cheesecake. 11/10
Great service and great food. Hands down best tomato bisque I've ever had!
Very good
Lunch was delicious 😋 Our server was friendly, tables were spaced apart for social distancing ❣
Fresh seafood!! In Iowa!!! Awesome happy hour, too (3-6 daily; drink specials and 1/2 priced oysters & delicious, delicious seafood tower.) Staff is also super sweet and good <3

This is an Iowa City Staple. I have loved St. Burch Tavern since it was Atlas. The atmosphere/vibes, amazing food, and awesome customer service make this the perfect place to celebrate or just sneak away to treat yourself.  From birthdays, prom, lunch dates on the patio, to graduation, promotions, and everything in between you can always get delicious food, clean service, great drinks, &  arguably one of the best happy hours.
Great atmosphere.. Great service.. Great food
Classic, little joint. Unique drinks and good food. Buffalo Chicken burrito is straight fire. 🔥🔥🔥

From start to finish, St Burch Tavern goes above and beyond.  Staff is attentive to service and cleanliness, and the food is fabulous.  Fresh oysters, king crab, lobster roll in Iowa City, 100 percent yes! Chloe, Christine, Lauren, Kevin and the rest of the staff were great. I would come back!!

It was such a treat to speak with the owner who actually cares about the food he is serving you. He has gone to great lengths to make sure it is honestly healthy and you know exactly what's in your dish! Waiter was so sweet and wore gloves and mask. Social distancing. I felt really safe there. Going back again with some friends this week!
The shrimp Gemelli Pasta is amazing. Actually everything is amazing. Soda lines need to be cleaned though.
Good food. A bit expensive but the service is really good
Small outdoor seating area right in the middle of downtown, great people watching spot. Helpful staff and a great happy hour!
Food was great!  Service was not.  Good food bad service! They changed the waiter this place just got my 3 star from 1 star live update!
Excellent food, excellent service!
Mushroom melt is my favorite on the menu, but you can't go wrong. No reservations so be sure to call ahead to see if they're busy.
Employees masked, extremely clean and being cleaned constantly and food was fantastic. Thanks for keeping us well fed and safe!
Amazing space, cocktails, and food! Gluten free accommodating just make sure to ask about what you're ordering :)
Slightly limited menu, and a bit pricy. But the food is good.
Order the white truffle fries and the tomato bisque.
Fantastic, service, atmosphere and oysters! Must go happy hour, or we'd have to sell an arm and a leg.
Eclectic food choices that were all delicious.
West coast oysters delicious! Also had the Burch Burger must have!
Food is great not over priced and great service. No complaints about this place.
The best part of my salad were the radishes. It’s pricey. The black bean burger was very good. The Mac and cheese was decent. It’s a nicer sit down place in the Iowa city downtown area.
Great staff and delicious food and cocktails.
Love the lobster roll
Great oysters, I think probably best in Iowa city. Their regular menu could be improved a bit though. Good service.
Chefs twist ruined the dishes. Never had a Philly I didn't like until today. Drinks tasted like perfume.

Super friendly staff! Everyone in masks and bartenders wearing gloves. Felt nice and safe. I had a summertime gin & tonic with a strawberry shrub and basil, very fresh and yummy! I haven't been since St. Burch took over Atlas. There was an oyster bar in the upstairs and a cool lower bar called "The den" with cool red lighting and a nice chill atmosphere. Would come back again to hang out down there and enjoy the vibes/ music. Bartender was was also very friendly downstairs Tonight! 🙂 Did not get a chance to eat, just 1 drink.

This is a cute little restaurant with quite tasty food! My boyfriend really enjoyed his burger, and I thoroughly enjoyed my shrimp. Don't let that little bowl fool you: it holds a LOT of shrimp! and it is very good. That being said, they have this sauce my son received with his chicken tenders that made them out of this world. Without that sauce they're just good. With the sauce: amazing. The queso dip was very good, but the chips tasted like they came from a grocery store bag. Not inedible by any means, but also not freshly made in-house. At least, they didn't have that freshly made taste. It was a little disappointing. Also a tad disappointing, while still very tasty, was the size of our cheddar bay biscuits. Perhaps Red Lobster has spoiled us, but the bites we were served had us wanting more. Otherwise, our service was great and sitting outside on the patio to eat was near perfect. Would eat here again.
This is my absolute favorite place in I.C.. great drinks, excellent service, and the den is such a great atmosphere. Can't wait to go back.

The shrimp and grits and Cesar salad were great but the Cheddar biscuits are not biscuits more like biscuit bites, very disappointed in the biscuits because they were small, bland and not fluffy. Also overpriced, $7 for 10 mini biscuits.

Great place for a romantic evening or a night out with friends. The service is very good. The wait staff is friendly and make great recommendations. Good atmosphere and the cocktails are all made perfectly.
i realize now that this is not a church.
Amazing service and exceptional food!
Great service and food
Great oysters.. but the drinks are overpriced. Sometimes that's necessary if you want the perfect Manhattan.
A good place to go for oysters.

Took 30 mins to get a table even though we had made reservations. 4 other couples had the same problem so it wasn't just that one table stayed too long after their dinner. They just planned poorly. Although they did give us free drinks when we complained.
Great food! Great atmosphere!

Best restaurant I have EVER been to. The aesthetic alone is enough reason to go. Not only is the food spectacular and the drinks magical, but the people that work there are out of this world!  Talk about H-O-S-P-I-T-A-L-I-T-Y. :)
Great atmosphere, Oyster Po Boy was really good.

Overall, the service was excellent and the drinks were superb. I did, however, order the $27 steak and it tasted like rubber, as if it was pulled from the abyss of abhorrent meats. Additionally, the "side" Caesar salad was approximately two bites worth of Dollar Tree-worthy lettuce and cheese. Long story short, go for drinks and a stereotypical "fancy" ambiance, but be prepared to get taken for a ride on the bland, overpriced food.
The food was phenomenal!
Unspeakable food and service.Great people.  I'd love to go back there when I can.
Always excellent food, drinks, and service. Highly recommend!
Quality food and great daily happy hour
Great food

The lemon tart with handmade lemon poppy seed ice cream is TO DIE FOR!!!  I wish I had taken a photo, but I ate it too fast! Our server Seth was really nice and very helpful/patient with ordering. He has superb hospitality skills. Plus they have happy hour from 3-6PM with half off drinks and oysters:)  An Edit: went again today and the sandwiches were not very good. This is a seafood place so maybe stick to that because it’s pretty fresh here. I had the ground meat sandwich but it was basically room temperature... The mulled wine however was awesome and the service yet again was excellent. I think our server was named Ian and he was really sweet and helpful.  Reminded again once we sat down how cute this place is... the bar would be an awesome place for a date!
Always amazing, check it out for great food and a cozy atmosphere.
Pretty good, but a little expensive for the quality of food and service.
Great service and top quality food!

They do amazing things with oysters and seafood. Cool atmosphere, great music, cocktails, generous portions, food that makes you clean your plate. Also the coffee... French press and delicious. A great addition to the Iowa City food scene, not to be missed.
Excellent, food and service!
Terrible service, took us 20 minutes to get a single drink on a medium night. The atmosphere is neat though.
Poor service

Made our first trip to St. Burch Tavern, I think the reason it took so long was all of the great eating places just within a few hundred feet of the place. The only thing that I knew about the place was that it was owned by the same folks as the Pullman Diner. (Should have been enough)  Upon entry it was bright and some really neat old U of I and Iowa City pictures. Our server was knowledgeable and bubbly. The menu was varied yet not overwhelming. One of the first things we noticed was the teamwork between the entire staff. From the managing partner, to the hostess , servers and bartender. We were there for lunch so I went for the jugular and decided to judge the St. Burch Tavern by its burger, believe it or not one of the toughest things to do well. The Burch burger which consists  Iowa corn-fed angus beef, bacon, raclette & white cheddar cheese, grilled onion, black truffle aioli put this burger in my current top two burgers anywhere.  My wife had the grilled cheese and tomato soup which was also very good. One of the biggest surprises at St. Burch was that they serve Intelligentsia coffee.  I know it was a dreary rainy day when we were there but I think they may have just as well been called the french press cafe as french press after french press was brought to many of the tables around us. We can’t wait to return to the St. Burch Tavern.
had no complaints about the sandwich but the fries were top tier. I highly recommend getting the French fries here, you won't regret it.
Excellent service, shout to Anthony! The seafood tower was delicious, the oysters and king crab were top notch!
Great Wait staff, Fabulous food & drinks. My first visit. Wonderful bartender. Leslie was awesome.

What a nice find in central Iowa City!  Oysters flown in twice a week!  I had a lunch of "pick 2" with the wild mushroom melt on toasted focaccia, paired with tomato bisque.  Best tomato soup I've had in years!
The lobster roll is to die for!!! Paper Plane is excellent! Staff is always lovely!
Good food, good service.

We had a reservation here for dinner after a football game. We arrived early but we were seated right away. We ordered 2 rounds of drinks before food came out but I understand they are busier than normal. Both cocktails I had were great and the server was attentive. The crab ravioli was excellent as well as my trout. We ended with the lemon tart which was perfect.
Great seafood dishes, especially the oyster Po boy and lobster Mac. Mixed drinks were amazing and beer selection was great.
The food was wonderful. The oyster poorboy and salmon chower was amazing. Live it
Mulled wine and atmosphere
Great food! Great staff. First time there and I'll go back again
New menu Recommend pork belly
My favorite place on earth.

This place is ultra cool, but still very welcoming. A couple friends and I went there on a very slow weekday night. It was just the three of us at the downstairs bar but the bartender was still super friendly and happy to serve us.
This is hands down the best place in Iowa city to go for a meal or a drink. their oysters are incredible and the wonderful staff make some of the best cocktails you will ever have.
Great den and upper restaurant!

Very nice den setting for a quiet evening with friends, family and colleagues. The food is good and the conversation better. The bartender has elephantine memory of patrons and their likes. And he is knowledgeable about the sports too.  The appetizers are good especially the shrimp in a curried sauce and the cheese curds. The entrees are decent and the salmon was delicious and succulent.  The potato puree was a bit thick and caked. Otherwise it was enjoyable.
Very good wines, salads & entrees in downtown Iowa City
The best shrimp cocktail in town! Good place for lunch, yummy drinks, great service, and cute interior. Head down to the Den for a cozy atmosphere and delicious cocktails!
Very friendly, attentive and helpful staffs! The sirloin steak, caesar salad and lobster mac are GREAT!!
Great food, cool place
Great food reasonable prices. Sat in the Den downstairs which has a neat hideaway vibe to it. 👍👍👍
Overall good quality. Bit often radically overpriced.
Small-ish menu, but amazing food! Also a great drink selection!
Great service, good food, catered nicely to children.
Very tasty spot with good steak, seafood, and burgers! Lovely drinks, too!
I had a good meal, but I have to rate it slightly low because I really miss Atlas
The Salmon chowder was the bomb.  There hot sauce withe the oysters is also amazing. Great and friendly service. Looking forward to going back.
Good tenderloin but it's no Atlas
First time there, great food, great service, great atmosphere, fantastic. Going to be one of my favorites in Iowa City.
Great oysters, long time Iowa City establishment - must visit
Slow service and mediocre food.
Happy hour oysters.
I'll come back for the seafood tower again!
Excellent diner on a Friday night - Many of the downtown restaurants were empty - but not here inside and out busy at 5:30 pm. We will be back again!
Happy hour (half priced oysters and seafood tower) ROCKS!

Best Burger I've ever had!!! I came here randomly as I was doing a cross country road trip and WOW!! what an amazing food this place had. The server was extremely warm & helpful. The burger was so juicy that I tried not to add anything to alter its taste. The waitress also recommended a hot sauce that I loved. Overall a great experience that anyone in the area must try.
Fabulous

Our server was so patient and pleasant. Checked on us enough but not too much because it took us a while to figure out what we wanted. He was very polite. It was our first time there and will definitely be back. I only ordered drinks and oysters and the oysters were delicious. He did a great job explaining the different kinds to us. He was very thorough.
Very cool experience,  I felt like I was in New Orleans.
Great drinks
Great place, wonderful dinner on the patio.

username: Come play in my mouse house

caption: Good food and good vibe to the place. A bit spend for lunch but the burger was really top-notch.

Amazing!  Perfect location with delightful patio seating.  Staff was the best I have experienced in all of Iowa.  Would highly recommend the Roasted Mushroom Melt with Roasted & marinated red pepper, goat cheese, caramelized onions, black truffle aioli, house made focaccia.. to die for!
Great place to eat. Good food and service was wonderful. Great place to hang out.
Love this place! The waitress we had was super attentive and friendly and the food and drinks were awesome too.
Great seafood! All the staff seemed to help each other and very friendly. Highly recommend.

This place is a fantastic and innovative restaurant that really stands out in Iowa City as one of its best, and even one of its most unique. The fish-fry inspired food and offerings of oysters/shrimp are all fantastic but I particularly love how they try to marry that east coasty seafood with midwestern-style american pub fare. Their takes on burgers, lobster rolls, mac and cheese are all top notch. Big recommend.  (Their other restaraunt, Pullmans, is still my all time fave, however!)

We were put at a little table between 2 larger rather loud parties.  Very inconsiderate of host I thought.  Nobody would want that table. I had a lobster roll which had no flavor what so ever.  We ordered a hot fudge sundae for dessert.  It was not hot fudge.  It was like that hard shell fake food ice cream topping. My husband had a steak sandwich.  He said it was good. I was very disappointed.  We really thought this place would be great.
I had the lobster mac and cheese which was Devine! Super rich and creamy! For dessert I had the lemon tart which was absolutely decadent served with a homemade lemon poppy seed ice cream ❤❤

Very good environment  maybe I have a bigger appetite than most people but they should say it feeds 1maybe a half a person the small tower   They say it serves 2 to 3 people The food was very good asked for saltine crackers they gave me Ritz crackers charge me $1.50 for maybe eight crackers and I asked for cocktail sauce charged me $.50 for the cocktail sauce  should’ve told me there was an additional charge  food tasty portions disappointing more communication would be good
I loved this restaurant.  Wonderful service (waitress was so interesting-harpist, environmentalist—. Food was excellent!
Try their special home made hot sauce for oysters if you dare. It is super spicy but out if this world. Other less spicy things are delicious as well.
Must try the burrito.
Everything is great
Good oysters
They were at the art festival downtown and decided to try them out. I had regular gyros which was like $10 personally I didn't like it. The meat was salty and sauce was very blend.

Nice patio, we had a pretty day for our visit and sat outside. Server let us have a leasurely late lunch. Food was prepared perfectly. Inside is a bit quirky but I can see the appeal for some. Kind of an old soda shop vibe. The menu was an interesting mix of things, I hope you like your cheese to be perfectly paired with the dish. What a good idea. The beer/wine list was similar, a little bit of everything for everyone. I enjoyed the cherry cider. And do yourself a favor and have the tatertot poutine to start.

Good selection for food.  Ordered the pork burger and was asked whether I wanted the “house chips” or fries, I selected the former.  Found what they meant was crisps!! Had I known I’d have gone for the fries! Other than that beer was good and nice place.

excellent service, excellent food. Never hesitate going there. you will love it We sat outside, great weather, nice and quiet this was a dessert we split. lemon curd with meringue,  a scoop of homemade poppyseed ice cream. It was a 5 stars
Nice upscale feel with upscale prices. The food was good and the service great.
It was ok
Awesome atmosphere, good service and good food.
This place is amazing. From the ambience to the food, great experience. Perfect for drinks or a date night.
Pricey
Really good
Food great. Drinks too much ice,

The food is incredible, and the atmosphere is lively and elegant. My wife and I sat at the tavern bar and dined. The chicken picatta was perfect, tender from the sous vide, but crisp skin from a flash fry.  My wife had the roasted mushroom melt, and it was impeccable. Our bartender was informative, and his technique was confident and well-practiced. Thank you, Chad, for great service. Cheers to the team, the chefs, and future success. My compliments all around, keep doing what you're doing!

Ceaser grilled chicken salad was average, not bad but somewhat bland and flat.  The white bean and kale soup was quite good, we'd get it again.  The service was poor.  Everyone was on the ball, hostess, table manager?, Food delivery etc BUT our waiter was way more interested in schmoozing than serving us.  I guess we weren't hipster enough.
Good selection for the whole family, nice patio with heaters
Fantastic cheese curds and great atmosphere. Downstairs den is really fun place to go at night.
Seafood here is seriously incredible. Easily one of my favorite places in Iowa City.
Lovely
This is a great oyster bar!!! Great environment and friendly staff.
Lobster bisque was great. Good variety of seafood. Drinks are decent. Menu has something for everyone. Great service--very attentive and helpful!
Happy hour was excellent!  Loved the oysters and seafood tower.

Wow. We certainly had a different experience than a lot of the other reviewers. New management? Great service and really delicious food. My  mom had a salad and soup and I had a salad. Both were great. Others around us seemed to be enjoying their food as well. Price was reasonable also. The food here is eclectic so lots of options for everyone. I had the impossible burger, others had trout or chicken. It was good. It was loud and difficult to hear. Service was great!

Very good! Pasta was perfectly cooked and dishes were well executed. Melt in your mouth cheese curds were a treat and the service was attentive. So many things to try on the menu and we'll definitely be back for the lobster roll.
Great place to visit and have dinner
Great service and great food!

Great menu selection. Interesting appetizers that deliver! Try the fried cheese curds, they are like little puffy clouds of cheese. We had the same very salad, which was marvelous. Simple flavors beautiful colors.

Service was five star. Food was four star, but only because I couldn't get what I wanted from the menu until after 4 p.m. and we were there for lunch. Having said that I sure recommend this spot to anyone who wants an elegant meal.  The prices for a bit high for my budget. So it won't be on my list high protein places to eat every week. But I absolutely recommend it for anyone celebrating a special occasion or just wanting I really delicious meal.
Outstanding lunch today!  Terrific service and excellent food.  We were a group of 5.  5 different orders.  All were amazing.
Great food and service
I had a great time. Amazingly fresh sea food

We love st burch! The staff always makes us feel special. The craft cocktails are delicious try the French 75 it's one of our favorites. We have loved any dish we have tried some of our go tos are the seafood tower, tatertot poutine, the prime rib and the fish & chips. Great spot for a chill lunch or a date night. Dont forget to go downstairs and check out the den super cool vibes and even more great drinks to try. Definitely wont disappoint.
All around good. The pork sandwich was real good, soup decent.
Excellent! There is a super great selection on the menu, and everything we ordered was delicious. The atmosphere and music were relaxing and upbeat, same for the staff. I highly recommend.

Atlas was one of our favorites. St. Burch kept a lot of what we liked with the new format and name. Excellent food, and several of the old favorites are still on the menu. The wait staff were attentive and friendly. The Den downstairs is quirky and fun.
Good food, friendly service, nice atmosphere
Loved the food and the environment there. Gets a little crowded on Friday nights but the food was absolutely delicious.
The staff are just wonderful, they make your visit a great one.
Good service. extremely small portions I ordered lobster roll and was 3 bites...
This place is a gem. I ordered soup and grilled cheese. Soooo good. Do not order this sandwich if on a diet. Also, the fries are to die for.
Great spot. One of the best in the city.
Nice place for dinner or drinks. Burger ban had so many sesame seeds

Their oysters and  sauté mussels were wonderful with a great variety of oysters tochoose from . The raw bar is right there with oysters being schucked in front of you, very knowledgeable staff making recommendations on regions and taste. I enjoyed this because I try a variety of oysters like I try wines.  The atmosphere was hip yet comfortable. The staff and service was some of the best. Had wonderful recommendations from the gentlemen running the oyster bar and their choices were spot on. From start to finish excellent. Not to forget their salted Carmel/ white chocolate mousse that came out with sprinkled candied bacon and apples and a small maple ice cream.
Bartender was awesome
The loose meat sandwich from your childhood only way better than you remember it.  Delicious!
Seafood mid continent! Oyster variety was cool! Delicious beer too!
Really great ambiance. Fantastic dishes. Super customer service.

Tasty cocktails and delicious food! The VooDoo shrimp is a personal favorite, and the steak salad. They fly in fresh seafood regularly which makes the raw bar a must try. Always good for lunch, drinks, or dinner!
The ceasar salad was perfection.  Also loved the seafood tower. Basement bar is the perfect dark space. Great ambiance perfect for a quick salad or a long lingering meal!

Food is pretty good, but both of the steaks at my table weren't cooked properly. Also way overpriced for what it is. I assume it will stay in business because the bar downstairs is a great feel and reasonably priced, but there's no reason to get dinner here unless you're trying to impress a date.

Wife and I just got back. Delicious deserts and great food. Adorable service. Tried the creme de menthe. Sweet. Good. Classic Iowa restaurant that will be packed during caucus time. Downstairs red room looks really cool and well try it next time. I like to come here for the banana split....But the new desert whatever it was called was fantastic.
#historic  great food. Ask about the decorations and the name, it's a wonderful story.
Friday night bartender at The Den (bar downstairs from the restaurant) was super nice and friendly. Had a cranberry mule cocktail that was delicious. Nice vibe and good for larger groups.
Excellent service and delicious oysters!
The seafood tower was mediocre but everyone else's food looked great!
Great staff and menu!
Hard to replace Atlas, but this place has some delicious stuff. Definitely worth trying, and I'll go back at least a few more times.
It's weird. The restaurant tries to be part oyster shack, part steakhouse, part family restaurant, part hipster diner and really fails to be any of them to a degree that justifies the prices
Awesome place for a unique drink and taste of IOWA! Our bartender Chad was the best!
Nice atmosphere, great service for a Saturday night and delicious food
Great food and staff. My friends and I always like to start out a great night at the DEN
Really good lobster roll.  Good atmosphere if you like small places.   Service was excellent and friendly.

Tailgated in the Den, which is the basement in Saint Burch Tavern.  The atmosphere is great.  It is a stone basement with a retro 70 vibe including old 70s beer lights/clocks and different sized punch bowl drinks.  They have local microbrewed beer to drink.  I had the tavern.  The meat was good, but there was too much bead for the amount of meat.  The bread was dry which kind of ruins the sandwich.  If the bread was steamed (perhaps just by putting the sandwich in tin foil) the sandwich would have tasted great.  The chips and onion dip was good as was the kale and bean soup.
Best pork tenderloin around!
Great drinks in a nice environment
Food and service was excellent.

My favorite bar in town. They have great drinks at good prices and well trained staff. Everytime I go downtown, I stop by St. Burch. They also have live music fairly regularly. Most of all the have good food. Perfect for a date spot. The atmosphere is friendly, clean and cool.
We only set at the bar...The Hudson cocktail is good and tasty oysters

Meh. That's all.  Meh. Oysters were edible, clams not so much.  No cocktail sauce and horseradish for the oysters.  Funky mignonette sauce. Option of sauces would be good. The weirdest thing is, for a supposed raw seafood bar place, most of the entrees aren't seafood based.  Go figure.

I was really hoping to enjoy the experience here based on what I’ve been hearing, but it was not good.  We sat at the bar in the basement, which was  probably a mistake on our part. It was a Saturday and the place was packed. A man walked up to us not 30 seconds after being seated telling us to be quiet because of an event in the other room. We hadn’t even said anything, but I sort of shrugged it off and we stayed quiet.  I ordered a seafood tower that was met immediately by fruit flies. Not to mention the seafood tower was hardly a tower. Wasn't nearly enough to share with three people. That being said, the seafood was good.  I really wanted to like this place. The atmosphere was great and the basement was cool. I will give it another try on a day not as hectic, but the fruit flies coupled with the food being underwhelming ruined the experience.

So I can't weigh in on the comparison to Atlas because I never made in there while it was still around. Although I must say St. Burch Tavern doesn't need to be compared because it holds its own.  I came here for lunch with some family who was visiting from out of town and everyone enjoyed their own option of the $10 dollar lunch special which was 1/2 a sandwich and salad. I opted for the mushroom melt sandwich with roasted mushrooms and goat cheese which had great flavor. For my salad I went with the Caesar salad which had lemon zest which added some great fresh flavor. Also don't forget to order the curds (they are the best I've ever had) and checkout the bar downstairs for a drink and some bumper pool.

Neat restaurant/bar. Upstairs/main floor is a straight up diner, but downstairs feels like a comfy cave with natural rock walls. Small menu but all are above average. Really enjoyed coffee brought to the table in a french press. Great relaxed atmosphere.
Nice place
Best grilled cheese I've ever had

outdoor seating was fine. Worst Bloody Mary ever. Did not drink it. Buffet food was cold. Mushroom chicken was tough enough to pound nails. Maybe it was a bad day, although Bloody Mary receipe needs overhaul!!!!!!!
Excellent Cocktails, polenta, Service, abs location.  good oysters and buffalo wings, among many other things.!

The food and cocktails were delicious. I got the Champagne Cocktail, Poutine appetizer and Shrimp Voodoo entree. My partner ordered the Burch Burger and house made chips. The service was quick and attentive, the waitress was very kind. The food was a little pricey which is the only reason I didn't give full 5 stars. But the whole experience was delightful.
Big menu and a wide variety

A must visit in Iowa City. The food here is always creative, approachable and cooked to perfection with the highest standard of quality. The vibe here is very cool. You need to visit "the Den" below for another cool experience. Be sure to stop in!

I have to say I was surprised by how much I liked this restaurant. The fish was fresh, the service was amazing, the atmosphere was new and fresh, definitely a step up from the previous restaurant at this location, and the drinks were out of this world fantastically made. It is honestly a rarity in Iowa City to find a bartender capable of making a proper cocktail and it was refreshing just to be able to experience one for once. However, on a sour note, the food was great but for the price and the portion sizes I thought it was nearing the point of not wanting to come back. Do not get me wrong I loved the food and our drinks, but after paying over 100$ for two people for 2 entrees and a pair of drinks each it was definitely on the pricy side given the amount of food you received. However please don't let this be the reason not to try it, I will be coming back, maybe not once a month but at least a few times a year
